21enum class WellKnownImport : uint8_t {
22 // Generic:
23 kUninstantiated,
24 kGeneric,
25 kLinkError,
26
28 // Compile-time "builtin" imports:
30 kFirstCompileTimeImport,
31
32 // JS String Builtins
33 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/js-string-builtins
34 // TODO(14179): Rename some of these to reflect the new import names.
35 kStringCast = kFirstCompileTimeImport,
36 kStringCharCodeAt,
37 kStringCodePointAt,
38 kStringCompare,
39 kStringConcat,
40 kStringEquals,
41 kStringFromCharCode,
42 kStringFromCodePoint,
43 kStringFromUtf8Array,
44 kStringFromWtf16Array,
45 kStringIntoUtf8Array,
46 kStringLength,
47 kStringMeasureUtf8,
48 kStringSubstring,
49 kStringTest,
50 kStringToUtf8Array,
51 kStringToWtf16Array,
52
53 kLastCompileTimeImport = kStringToWtf16Array,
55 // End of compile-time "builtin" imports.
57
58 // DataView methods:
59 kDataViewGetBigInt64,
60 kDataViewGetBigUint64,
61 kDataViewGetFloat32,
62 kDataViewGetFloat64,
63 kDataViewGetInt8,
64 kDataViewGetInt16,
65 kDataViewGetInt32,
66 kDataViewGetUint8,
67 kDataViewGetUint16,
68 kDataViewGetUint32,
69 kDataViewSetBigInt64,
70 kDataViewSetBigUint64,
71 kDataViewSetFloat32,
72 kDataViewSetFloat64,
73 kDataViewSetInt8,
74 kDataViewSetInt16,
75 kDataViewSetInt32,
76 kDataViewSetUint8,
77 kDataViewSetUint16,
78 kDataViewSetUint32,
79 kDataViewByteLength,
80
81 // String-related functions:
82 kDoubleToString,
83 kIntToString,
84 kParseFloat,
85
86 kStringIndexOf,
87 kStringIndexOfImported,
88 kStringToLocaleLowerCaseStringref,
89 kStringToLowerCaseStringref,
90 kStringToLowerCaseImported,
91 // Fast API calls:
92 kFastAPICall,
93};

98const char* WellKnownImportName(WellKnownImport wki);

100inline bool IsCompileTimeImport(WellKnownImport wki) {
101 using T = std::underlying_type_t<WellKnownImport>;
102 T num = static_cast<T>(wki);
103 constexpr T kFirst = static_cast<T>(WellKnownImport::kFirstCompileTimeImport);
104 constexpr T kLast = static_cast<T>(WellKnownImport::kLastCompileTimeImport);
105 return kFirst <= num && num <= kLast;
106}
107
108class WellKnownImportsList {
109 public:
110 enum class UpdateResult : bool { kFoundIncompatibility, kOK };
111
112 WellKnownImportsList() = default;
113
114 // Regular initialization. Allocates size-dependent internal data.
115 void Initialize(int size) {
116#if DEBUG
117 DCHECK_EQ(-1, size_);
118 size_ = size;
119#endif
120 static_assert(static_cast<int>(WellKnownImport::kUninstantiated) == 0);
121 statuses_ = std::make_unique<std::atomic<WellKnownImport>[]>(size);
122#if !defined(__cpp_lib_atomic_value_initialization) || \
123 __cpp_lib_atomic_value_initialization < 201911L
124 for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
125 std::atomic_init(&statuses_.get()[i], WellKnownImport::kUninstantiated);
126 }
127#endif
128 }
129
130 // Intended for deserialization. Does not check consistency with code.
131 void Initialize(base::Vector<const WellKnownImport> entries);
132
133 WellKnownImport get(int index) const {
134 DCHECK_LT(index, size_);
135 return statuses_[index].load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
136 }
137
138 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT UpdateResult
139 Update(base::Vector<WellKnownImport> entries);
140
141 // If you need this mutex and the NativeModule's allocation_mutex_, always
142 // get the latter first.
143 base::Mutex* mutex() { return &mutex_; }
144
145 private:
146 // This mutex guards {statuses_}, for operations that need to ensure that
147 // they see a consistent view of {statuses_} for some period of time.
148 base::Mutex mutex_;
149 std::unique_ptr<std::atomic<WellKnownImport>[]> statuses_;
150
151#if DEBUG
152 int size_{-1};
153#endif
154};
